00:22:47,250 --> 00:22:48,331
And we also found that it appealed

442
00:22:48,371 --> 00:22:50,533
to a specific subset of our game base.

443
00:22:51,796 --> 00:22:53,897
So the people who were interested in submitting ideas

444
00:22:54,057 --> 00:22:56,138
were largely those who were already socially quite mobile,

445
00:22:56,158 --> 00:22:57,878
they were communicating on social media.

446
00:22:58,319 --> 00:22:59,259
There are two reasons for that.

447
00:22:59,479 --> 00:23:01,420
It makes sense that those people who were willing to talk

448
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,020
and spend a lot of time outside of the game,

449
00:23:03,300 --> 00:23:04,041
talking to each other,

450
00:23:04,301 --> 00:23:06,942
also willing to kind of write a lot of stuff and relapse.

